The paper deals with the geometric median problem, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also presents algorithms that involve optimization techniques, such as interior point methods and stochastic subgradient descent, which are commonly used in cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the complexity of the algorithms, which is related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
